<div class='talk-article talk-article--main' id='talk' itemscope itemtype='http://schema.org/VideoObject'>
<link href='http://www.ted.com/talks/mark_pagel_how_language_transformed_humanity' itemprop='url'>
<meta content='How language transformed humanity' itemprop='name'>
<meta content='Biologist Mark Pagel shares an intriguing theory about why humans evolved our complex system of language. He suggests that language is a piece of "social technology" that allowed early human tribes to access a powerful new tool: cooperation.' itemprop='description'>
<meta content='PT20M10S' itemprop='duration'>
<link content='https://tedcdnpi-a.akamaihd.net/r/tedcdnpe-a.akamaihd.net/images/ted/b8e2d0127ed9ab310710eda04e92169dd9be7435_1600x1200.jpg?quality=95&amp;w=480' itemprop='thumbnailUrl'>
<span itemprop='author' itemscope itemtype='http://schema.org/Person'>
<link href='/speakers/mark_pagel' itemprop='url'>
<meta content='Mark Pagel' itemprop='name'>
<link href='http://tedcdnpe-a.akamaihd.net/images/ted/fad2b242f46da8f2a9430497a50a80afde8445cc_254x191.jpg' itemprop='image'>
</span>
<link href='https://embed-ssl.ted.com/talks/mark_pagel_how_language_transformed_humanity.html' itemprop='embedURL'>
